m12f4 x5d h2f y1be6 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTE.—&quot;After </div><div class="t m792 xb h2d y1be6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the remarkable exhibition of the power of God, </div><div class="t m35f x11 h2d y1a14 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jonathan could not believe that his father would still harm David, </div><div class="t m3bf x11 h2d y1f0a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">since this would be manifest rebellion against God. But David was </div><div class="t m1cc x11 h2d y1eea ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">not convinced. With intense earnestness he declared to Jonathan, &apos;As </div><div class="t m403 x11 h2d y1343 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Lord liveth, and as thy soul liveth, there is but a step between me </div><div class="t m1dc x11 h2d y17c2 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and death.&apos; &quot;—&quot;Patriarchs and ProphetS,&quot; p. 654. </div><div class="t m2b6 x5d h2d y64c ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m7d7 x28 h2d y64c ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What plan did David propose in order to find out what Saul&apos;s </div><div class="t mf42 x11 h2d y1c3d ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">intentions were toward him? Verses 5-7. </div><div class="t ma2 x5d h2d y1b3f ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m167 x28 h2d y1eec ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What covenant was made between David and Jonathan? How </div><div class="t m407 x11 h2d y17e1 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">was Jonathan to let David know what Saul did? Verses 16-23. </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
